<br>
First try:  Big DD pull, air pet on dino, keep just out ahead of him.  This worked fairly well for a little while, but he finally turned to the pet.  I laid in a few nukes trying to get him back after me, but he just wouldn't even look at me again.  Hit report health since I figured I would have to chain, and the pet was at 6%.  Gate.<br>
<br>
Second try:  Strict chaincasting of earth pets.  This one was going fairly well, and I had him over half way down when he rushed over and gave me a smack that disrupted the pet I was casting.  Time I moved away and started to cast another he managed to drop the one that was up.  Tap ring, tap boots, run like hell, gate.<br>
<br>
Third try:  Mix of the first two times.  I had just gotten the water staff and 54 water pet, so I just had to try that pet.  Big DD pull, pet on him, trailed him once around the island before he turned to pet.  Chained pet and he chased me 3 times around before he turned.  Next pet he chased me 5 times around before he turned.  Each time I suicided a pet, it was building up way more aggro onto me and he would just chase me for a longer time...and those backstabs were starting to add up.  4th pet up and he was chasing me forever.  Finally he turned away from me, and I ran back to get in range for pet commands...but he was walking away!  I still had mana left for a couple of nukes, but I like to see something walking helplessly away with my pet tearing it apart (Satisfying after all those times of being at the death walk for the zone with a mob or two beating on me.  hehe)  Sadly, though, I went LD right before he fell, so I missed the most glorious part of the battle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubarbel0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barbel0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(4/4/01 8:03:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dino</span><hr size=1> I tried this guy yesterday with my new water pet. Probably around 15 minutes fight, 7 pets used, 1 free bolt of burnt wood staff during each aggro on pet. 5 first pets died fast, 6th one lasted kiting 2-3 minutes, and finally 7th one lasted during 4 or 5 last minutes with big aggro. <br>
